The paper discusses a new system for Nearest Neighbor(s) search, which is a fundamental computational primitive in many areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the challenges of handling online query/update requests in high-dimensional spaces, which is a common problem in these subfields. Therefore, it is likely that the paper belongs to one or more of these sub-categories.
